60.1	Where_the_Wild_Things_Are_(film)	Where the Wild Things Are (film)	Where the Wild Things Are is a 2009 American fantasy drama film directed by Spike Jonze and adapted from Maurice Sendak's 1963 children's book Where the Wild Things Are. It combines live action, performers in costumes, animatronics, and computer-generated imagery (CGI). The film stars Max Records, and features the voices of James Gandolfini, Paul Dano, Lauren Ambrose, Forest Whitaker, Catherine O'Hara and Chris Cooper. The film centers around a lonely eight-year-old boy named Max who sails away to an island inhabited by creatures known as the "Wild Things", who declare Max their king.	http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/en/thumb/7/7b/Wherethewildthingsare.jpg/220px-Wherethewildthingsare.jpg
